ily%20and%20friends%20from%20the%20Alps%2C%20according%20to%20the%20local%20news%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20actual%20charge%20was%20much%20higher%20%E2%80%94%20around%20%24143%2C000%20for%209.5%20gigabytes%20of%20data%20used%20overseas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fadvisor%2Fbusiness%2Faverage-salary-by-state%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20Forbes%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20average%20annual%20salary%20in%20Florida%20is%20%2455%2C980%2C%20making%20the%20bill%20more%20than%20twice%20what%20an%20average%20worker%20makes%20each%20year%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemund%20had%20incurred%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20daily%20roaming%20charges%20because%20his%20phone%20was%20not%20set%20up%20for%20international%20roaming%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20US%20customers'%20domestic%20plans%20do%20not%20cover%20usage%20abroad%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fcc.gov%2Finternational-roaming%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20Communications%20Commission.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemund%20said%20he%20contacted%20T-Mobile%2C%20which%20confirmed%20the%20bill%20was%20indeed%20what%20he%20owed%2C%20per%20ABC%20Action%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemund%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERemund%20enlisted%20an%20attorney%2C%20who%20wrote%20letters%20to%20T-Mobile's%20president%20hoping%20for%20a%20response%2C%20the%20local%20outlet%20reported.%20The%20attorney%20also%20contacted%20ABC%20Action%20News%2C%20which%20subsequently%20contacted%20T-Mobiles's%20corporate%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20provided%20to%20BI%20by%20email%2C%20a%20T-Mobile%20spokesperson%20confirmed%20that%20the%20carrier%20agreed%20to%20credit%20Remund's%20account%20for%20the%20entire%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20shouldn't%20have%20happened%20and%20we%20fully%20credited%20the%2