20noticeable%20on%20the%20tail%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20report%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets.publishing.service.gov.uk%2Fmedia%2F661e3918d4a839725cbd3d78%2FAirbus_A321-253NX_G-OATW_06-24.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAir%20Accidents%20Investigation%20Branch%3C%2Fa%3E%20(AAIB).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20the%20windowpanes%20were%20completely%20removed%2C%20while%20the%20third%20window%20was%20missing%20the%20inner%20pane%20and%20a%20rubber%20seal%2C%20and%20a%20fourth%20window%20was%20damaged%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20nine%20passengers%20and%2011%20crew%20on%20board.%20None%20of%20them%20reported%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aircraft%20was%20originally%20used%20by%20the%20British%20government.%20It%20was%20later%20sold%20to%20Titan%20Airways%2C%20which%20describes%20itself%20as%20a%20charter%20airline%20specializing%20in%20VIP%20and%20corporate%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Telegraph%20reported%20that%20Charles%20and%20Camilla%20had%20traveled%20in%20the%20same%20aircraft%20during%20their%20visit%20to%20France%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221777%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22King%20Charles%20III%20and%20Queen%20Camilla%20plane%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66224fd520b15f0ff42970b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKing%20Charles%20III%20and%20Queen%20Camilla%20disembark%20the%20plane%20at%20Orly%20Airport%20on%20September%2020%2C%202023%20in%20Paris%2C%20France.%3Cp%3ETim%20Rooke%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20also%20been%20used%20by%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20and%20James%20Cleverly%2C%20the%20UK's%20Foreign%20Secretary%2C%20the%20outlet%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuckingham%20Palace%20declined%20to%20comment%20when%20contacted%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AAIB%20report%20identified%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20damage%3A%20The%20windows%20had%20been%20exposed%20to%20high-intensity%20lights%20when%20the%20aircraft%20was%20used%20to%20film%20a%20commercial%20at%20London's%20Stansted%20Airport%20the%20day%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lights%2C%20used%20to%20convey%20a%20sunrise%2C%20had%20been%20aimed%20at%20the%20windows%20for%20several%20hours%20at%20a%20time%2C%20the%20report%20said.%20They%20had%20a%20combined%20capacity%20of%2072%2C000%20watts%2C%20which%20is%20more%20than%20seven%20hundred%20times%20more%20powerful%20than%20a%20standard%20light%20bulb%2C%20The%20Telegraph%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221684%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22plane%20damage%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6622507e49058e669357935a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221126%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20image%20by%20the%20Air%20Accidents%20Investigation%20Branch%20shows%20the%20damage%20caused.%3Cp%3EAir%20Accidents%20Investigation%20Branch%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20suggestion%20in%20the%20AAIB%20report%20that%20manufacturing%20issues%20contributed%20to%20the%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20aircraft%20lost%20windowpanes%2C%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20wind%20was%20shooting%20through%20the%20cabin%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20scratch%20panes%20remained%20in%20place%20so%20there%20was%20no%20direct%2C%20unrestricted%20aperture%20between%20the%20passenger%20cabin%20and%20the%20outside%20air%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%2C%20noting%20the%20amount%20of%20leaking%20air%20was%20not%20enough%20to%20trigger%20a%20pressurization%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20a%20Titan%20Airways%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20aviation%20industry%20as%20a%20whole%20will%20benefit%20from%20the%20lessons%20learnt%20from%20this%20event.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20also%20pleased%20to%20hear%20that%20our%20colleagues%20at%20Airbus%20will%20be%20circulating%20further%20information%20to%20its%20worldwide%20customer%20base%2C%20highlighting%20the%20potential%20damage%20that%20can%20be%20caused%20by%20high-intensity%20lighting%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbus%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20an%20aircraft%20has%20sustained%20damage%20from%20strong%20lighting%20on%20a%20film%20set.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20one%20other%20Airbus%20and%20three%20Boeing%20planes%20had%20previously%20reported%20damaged%20windows%20during%20respective%20filming%20events%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20knowledge%20of%20these%20incidents%20previously%20wasn't%20widespread.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDamage%20to%20one%20of%20the%20Boeing%20planes%20was%20significant.%20A%20hole%20burned%20through%20one%20of%20the%20windows%20while%20five%20other%20windows%20were%20deformed%20after%202%2C000W%20lights%20were%20used%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202020%2C%20Boeing%20released%20a%20statement%20advising%20against%20the%20use%20of%20high-intensity%20lights%2C%20the%20report%20added.%20If%20high-intensity%20lights%20were%20used%2C%20it%20suggested%20keeping%20use%20to%20a%20minimum%20and%20away%20from%20windows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwindows-fell-off-airbus-plane-used-king-charles-camilla-titan-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713534321000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6622559949058e66935793ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwindows-fell-off-airbus-plane-used-king-charles-camilla-titan-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Windowpanes%20fell%20off%20the%20Titan%20Airways%20Airbus%20aircraft%20during%20flight%20while%20it%20was%20on%20its%20way%20to%20Florida.%22%